1
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:45,533
[This drama is fictional, and any resemblance
to real people or events is coincidental.]

2
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,467
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,576
Oh, my.

4
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,909
Your skin is so fair.

5
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:16,000
Oh my goodness.

6
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,209
It's been so long.

7
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:15,000
My friend.

8
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:39,376
My friend, what's going on here?

9
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:41,100
Friend?

10
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:47,900
This is Baek Hye Ji.

11
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:50,743
My friend!

12
00:02:50,767 --> 00:02:52,900
You're still the same.

13
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:00,509
Uh, I have something to
talk about with my friend.

14
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:03,067
Oh, okay, go ahead.

15
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,909
Excuse me.

16
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:08,567
Yes?

17
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,943
You dropped something.

18
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:25,833
Something important.

19
00:03:29,967 --> 00:03:32,343
Oh! You're right.

20
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:35,876
How could you drop something so important?

21
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:38,233
- People must be waiting.
- Yes.

22
00:03:39,867 --> 00:03:41,467
Hurry up and go.

23
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,867
See you later.

24
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:50,533
Muchang Strawberries?

25
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:58,276
How did you know I was here?

26
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:00,643
Did Ga Seon Yeong send you?

27
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:04,843
Yeong Ran, there are
no secrets in this world.

28
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:07,309
And you're being so cold-hearted.

29
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,843
What's with Ga Seon Yeong?

30
00:04:09,867 --> 00:04:11,733
She's your daughter.

31
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:16,176
Just kidding.

32
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:19,676
But if the professor finds out you're here,

33
00:04:19,700 --> 00:04:22,667
she said she'd reward me handsomely.

34
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,300
That part is true.

35
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:36,843
What do you really want, Ms. Baek Hye Ji?

36
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:39,509
Why should I care?

37
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:43,433
The reward is what the giver decides.

38
00:04:44,672 --> 00:04:48,343
Miss, all is ready!

39
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:50,743
Friend, what day is it today?

40
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:53,509
I couldn't even eat a meal
coming all the way here.

41
00:04:53,510 --> 00:05:03,498
Officail Website : kissasia.id

42
00:05:03,522 --> 00:05:13,510
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

43
00:04:53,533 --> 00:04:55,167
Great!

44
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:59,176
Let's finish our talk before leaving.

45
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,243
What talk?

46
00:05:00,267 --> 00:05:02,109
How much do you want?

47
00:05:02,133 --> 00:05:04,933
How much will it take for you
to shut up and leave quietly?

48
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:10,043
Our Yeong Ran

49
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:14,209
has become a chaebol wife,
but you haven't changed at all.

50
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:16,109
No,

51
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:19,043
should I call you Ms. Bu Se Mi now?

52
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:21,143
Answer me first.

53
00:05:21,167 --> 00:05:23,100
Tell me what you want.

54
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,943
A billion won?

55
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,543
Are you serious?

56
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:31,609
No.

57
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:33,233
Ten billion won?

58
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:36,233
You want to die, huh?

59
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:38,276
Yeong Ran.

60
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,276
You're being awfully casual with me now.

61
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:44,209
Yeong Ran, I told you.

62
00:05:44,233 --> 00:05:47,076
Let's eat, drink coffee,
and watch movies together.

63
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:49,276
That's all I want.

64
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:52,009
Of course, you'll pay for everything.

65
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:54,867
Now, we're really
friends from today, right?

66
00:05:59,267 --> 00:06:05,200
Or should I have a serious talk
with the Muchang strawberry guy?

67
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:13,533
I've made a friend now too.

68
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:18,100
I'm leaving now. I'm hungry.

69
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:22,600
Please don't do anything foolish.

70
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:27,967
I'm asking you, friend.

71
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:31,267
Okay.

72
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,500
How in the world did Baek Hye Ji find me?

73
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,343
Get ready, folks.

74
00:06:59,367 --> 00:07:01,776
She's out!

75
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,543
She's here. Get ready.

76
00:07:05,567 --> 00:07:07,376
Ms. Bu Se Mi.

77
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,933
Welcome!

78
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,709
Well, you are treating us.

79
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,409
[Welcome, Ms. Bu Se Mi]
We couldn't just stand by.

80
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:21,276
Meals and gifts under 50,000 won
don't violate ethics laws.

81
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:22,343
So this banner

82
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:24,776
cost 40,000 won from
our regular vendor for village events,

83
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,976
and these fireworks were delivered
in the early morning for 9,800 won.

84
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:32,000
Total 49,800 won. A safe solution.

85
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:39,776
Ms. Bu Se Mi, this is
our heartfelt gesture.

86
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,000
We love you.

87
00:07:43,037 --> 00:07:44,888
Fireworks!

88
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:56,409
Everyone, let's eat.

89
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:58,143
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

90
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,643
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

91
00:07:59,667 --> 00:08:01,643
Please have your meal
before the noodles get soggy.

92
00:08:01,667 --> 00:08:03,509
Sit here.

93
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:06,009
Miss, look at that bounce house over there.

94
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:08,109
The kids love it.

95
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,743
You should check it out.

96
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:11,143
Come this way.

97
00:08:11,167 --> 00:08:13,009
- Friend.
- Wait, Ms. Bu's friend.

98
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:15,267
Join us for a meal.

99
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:20,533
Wait, did you come all the way
from Seoul to Muchang just to see her?

100
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,876
Everyone, having fun?

101
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:25,609
- Yes.
- Yes.

102
00:08:25,633 --> 00:08:27,043
Miss Bu Se Mi is the best!

103
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:30,300
- Miss Bu Se Mi is the best!
- Miss Bu Se Mi is the best!

104
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,676
The best!

105
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:37,009
Miss, today feels like my birthday.

106
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:39,067
This is so much fun.

107
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:42,733
This is for you.

108
00:08:46,112 --> 00:08:49,480
I'm back, guys!

109
00:08:49,504 --> 00:08:51,368
Are you ready?

110
00:08:51,392 --> 00:08:54,153
Come on, climb up.

111
00:08:58,133 --> 00:08:59,743
What?

112
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,567
Why is the light on?

113
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:16,843
No.

114
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:19,943
Baek Hye Ji!

115
00:09:19,967 --> 00:09:21,309
[Not on my side: It's going well, right?]

116
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,200
It's going well, right?

117
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,867
Oh, it looks delicious.

118
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:31,300
Wow, you've worked so
hard preparing for today.

119
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:33,776
- Ju Won's father.
- Yes.

120
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:37,233
We're not just here to eat today, right?

121
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:41,300
Shouldn't we verify her?

122
00:09:42,167 --> 00:09:43,767
Wait a second.

123
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:51,533
- Yeah.
- Shouldn't we verify her?

124
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:57,176
Speaking from a police perspective,
people aren't always trustworthy.

125
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,976
Do we really need to verify her?

126
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,676
She seems fine to me.

127
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,743
Hey, Jeong Hwa.

128
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:04,876
You know you're bad
at judging people, right?

129
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,309
Isn't that right, PTA President?

130
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:08,100
But she's kind.

131
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,600
Is she?

132
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,109
By the way, Miss.
Do you prefer jjamppong or jajangmyeon?

133
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:19,609
I enjoy both equally.

134
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:21,376
That's hard to choose.

135
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,200
Mixed noodles. Just choose mixed noodles.

136
00:10:27,767 --> 00:10:29,533
Enjoy your meal.

137
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:34,967
Miss.

138
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:38,709
This tastes great.

139
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:40,009
- Enjoy your meal.
- Yes.

140
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:44,109
Well, my younger sister graduated from
Iseon Women's University's business school.

141
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:47,876
When I went to her graduation,
the building was really cool.

142
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,076
Oh.

143
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:51,609
The business school building?

144
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,643
Yeah.

145
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:55,776
The windows there are really big, right?

146
00:10:55,800 --> 00:11:01,076
When I used to attend classes there,
the sunlight would pour in,

147
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:03,343
and I would get really sleepy.

148
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:04,676
That's right.

149
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,809
I think my younger sister, Seung Hee,
also mentioned something like that.

150
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,976
Wait, do you know Pyo Seung Hee?

151
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,433
She's a reporter at GNA now.

152
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:15,867
Pyo Seung Hee.

153
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:19,176
I only know her face.

154
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:23,243
Seung Hee had such pretty eyes, remember?

155
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:26,009
Yeah, that's right.

156
00:11:26,033 --> 00:11:28,700
Oh, Lord.

157
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:32,576
Please finish your meal quickly.

158
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,909
Did Seung Hee have beautiful eyes?

159
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:36,809
She suddenly became prettier.

160
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:39,443
During the summer vacation of 3rd grade.

161
00:11:39,467 --> 00:11:42,276
Oh right.

162
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:45,443
Miss, then Seung Hee...

163
00:11:45,467 --> 00:11:47,843
Right, right. Jeong Woo.

164
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:49,076
Everyone.

165
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:51,976
I have some good news to share today.

166
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,643
The rumor that Ms. Bu Se Mi has come to

167
00:11:53,667 --> 00:11:58,243
our Muchang Iseon Kindergarten has spread
throughout the whole town of Muchang,

168
00:11:58,267 --> 00:12:02,167
and we plan to have more students
starting next week.

169
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:07,467
Miss, please say a few words.

170
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:14,243
Although this is a welcome party for me,

171
00:12:14,267 --> 00:12:19,243
I'm so grateful for the wholehearted
welcome you've all given me.

172
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:22,176
I actually heard some bad things

173
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,800
about the previous teachers
from Ju Won's father.

174
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:31,543
I understand you couldn't open up to me
because the children were hurt by them.

175
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:35,476
But I'm definitely different from them.

176
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,933
I always keep my promises.

177
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:42,276
Please watch and see.

178
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,676
Alright, let's watch.

179
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:47,743
- Bu Se Mi!
- Bu Se Mi!

180
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:51,076
Now, shall we all have a drink?

181
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,509
- Yes.
- Let's drink.

182
00:12:52,533 --> 00:12:54,333
- Fill the glasses.
- Okay.

183
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,009
Ms. Bu's friend?

184
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,833
- Ms. Bu's friend?
- Huh?

185
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:07,209
Wait, so you two are alumni
from Iseon Women's University?

186
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:09,043
The early childhood education department?

187
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:11,109
Ah...

188
00:13:11,133 --> 00:13:13,876
- We...
- I majored in ballet.

189
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:15,409
- Wow.
- Ballet?

190
00:13:15,433 --> 00:13:16,809
Should I show you?

191
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,500
Right now?

192
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:25,067
Oh my, oh my.

193
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,133
Wow.

194
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,043
Wow.

195
00:13:31,067 --> 00:13:32,044
Wait, that... That...

196
00:13:32,068 --> 00:13:34,543
Are you really taking off socks
at the dinner table...

197
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:35,809
What are you doing?

198
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:37,609
Goodness, how eccentric.

199
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:40,000
- Seriously.
- What's that?

200
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,700
1473.

201
00:13:47,467 --> 00:13:48,809
1473? What's that?

202
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,543
Press 1473.

203
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:53,967
Should I... Should I press it?

204
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,876
Keep the phone steady and film properly.

205
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,533
A video?

206
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:31,343
♫ It's the start of our story ♫

207
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:36,343
♫ Like fairy tale protagonists ♫

208
00:14:36,367 --> 00:14:38,843
♫ You and I ♫

209
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:45,176
♫ Smiling as we promise eternity ♫

210
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,743
♫ Close your eyes ♫

211
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:51,476
♫ The time we've dreamed of ♫

212
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:56,576
♫ Feel it, this happiness ♫

213
00:14:56,600 --> 00:15:01,476
♫ Melody, shall we dance ♫

214
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:08,076
♫ The happiest in the world ♫

215
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,733
♫ Us ♫

216
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,867
[Attorney Lee]

217
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:39,143
♫ The promise I wrote
on the first page is this ♫

218
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:46,909
♫ I love you, I'll never
miss a day to say it ♫

219
00:15:46,933 --> 00:15:47,910
Yes, Attorney Lee.

220
00:15:47,934 --> 00:15:49,076
Madam.

221
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:52,000
Is Baek Hye Ji there?

222
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:57,167
How on earth did Ms.
Baek Hye Ji know I'm here?

223
00:15:58,733 --> 00:16:00,243
Where did the information leak from?

224
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:02,000
I'm sorry.

225
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:06,176
I'll first check if the information
leaked to Ga Seon Yeong.

226
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,443
Understood.

227
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:11,676
Now most people in
Muchang seem to trust me.

228
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,376
Let's gradually start our plan.

229
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,476
Alright.

230
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,176
Then I'll...

231
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,800
Hello?

232
00:16:21,167 --> 00:16:23,867
She's not just a Madam anymore,
almost a Chairman now.

233
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,867
They are not just a
couple, they're twins, twins.

234
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:33,500
Start with the Ga Seon Woo video.

235
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:37,076
[Jeon Dong Min, 29-year-old P.E. teacher,
'extra', fortunately doesn't seem to recognize me]

236
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,000
Jeon Dong Min.

237
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,433
Looks like only one person remains?

238
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:49,543
♪ Life is ♪

239
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:52,076
♪ Just this and that ♪

240
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:57,300
♪ There is, because we'll be happy ♪

241
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:01,909
♪ If we laugh like a child ♪

242
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:05,309
♪ If we stay together ♪

243
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:09,600
♪ We'll all become happy ♪

244
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:16,276
♪ If we look at each other
while eating delicious food ♪

245
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,643
♪ Eh-eladiya ♪

246
00:17:18,667 --> 00:17:21,667
♪ Let's laugh ♪

247
00:17:25,100 --> 00:17:26,909
Ju Won's father.

248
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:29,543
I think you have something
to discuss with me.

249
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:30,776
Pardon?

250
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,909
I have nothing to discuss.

251
00:17:32,933 --> 00:17:35,043
But you should have.

252
00:17:35,067 --> 00:17:36,476
About what?

253
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:39,076
Well... About earlier.

254
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:43,067
Oh, that? It's nothing special.

255
00:17:48,033 --> 00:17:53,100
Hey!

256
00:17:53,867 --> 00:17:55,809
Hey!

257
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:58,900
Turn off the music!

258
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:02,343
Hello.

259
00:18:02,367 --> 00:18:07,133
Ya, ya, ya.

260
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:12,443
You never invite me.

261
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:15,676
Give me the mic, sis.

262
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:18,009
This punk, who did...

263
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:22,333
Why? Let's hang out.

264
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:27,333
Why do you always leave me out?

265
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:31,376
Ah, mic test.

266
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,609
Yes.

267
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:35,643
As a way to welcome

268
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:39,843
our new teacher, Ms. Bu Se Mi,

269
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:45,309
to Iseon Kindergarten,
the only one in Muchang,

270
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:47,733
I'll sing a song.

271
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:51,009
Jeez, he's ruining my appetite.

272
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,633
Play the music.

273
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,409
Hello.

274
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:57,676
As a native of Muchang,

275
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:02,009
I, Kang Seong Tae, of Muchang
Development Committee, greet you all.

276
00:19:02,033 --> 00:19:03,843
I am

277
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:06,800
a very, very emotional guy, by the way.

278
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:17,073
♪ Yeah ♪

279
00:19:17,097 --> 00:19:21,543
♪ I might be drunk ♪

280
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,300
I met eyes with him.

281
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:28,709
♪ It might be a mistake ♪

282
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:34,576
♪ By morning it'll fade away ♪

283
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:37,643
♪ I won't remember ♪

284
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:41,643
♪ You might worry ♪

285
00:19:41,667 --> 00:19:44,876
♪ But I must tell you tonight ♪

286
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:46,633
This is the worst.

287
00:19:47,867 --> 00:19:52,043
♪ There's something I must say ♪

288
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:55,376
Hey, this isn't working.
Plug it quickly! Who turned it off?

289
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,676
Hey, plug this fast! Who turned it off?

290
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:58,809
I have something to say.
There's something I need to say tonight.

291
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,043
Who turned it off?
My emotions are at their peak right now.

292
00:20:00,067 --> 00:20:03,743
- Who turned this off?
- Kang Seong Tae, you're drunk.

293
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:06,009
I can't understand anything you're saying.

294
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:08,600
None of us can understand you either.

295
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:17,000
Do you hate me that much?

296
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:23,633
Do you hate my singing that much?

297
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,709
You there, Dongwaru.

298
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:31,609
Don't you know our
contract renews next year?

299
00:20:31,633 --> 00:20:33,009
What are you talking about?

300
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,243
I was just about to dance.

301
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:37,633
Why are you playing
tambourine for a ballad?

302
00:20:39,033 --> 00:20:40,743
Ms. Kim Hye Jeong, Lee Jun's mom.

303
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:44,709
Do you know how much meat I buy
from that butcher shop monthly?

304
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:46,309
- Know or not?
- I don't know.

305
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:48,700
Jeez, you don't know?

306
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,609
Everyone lives off me,

307
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,509
yet why do you ignore me?

308
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:56,409
Why are you ignoring me?

309
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:59,076
What did I do so wrong?

310
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:00,909
Ugh, seriously, he's

311
00:21:00,933 --> 00:21:02,800
Mr. Kang Seong Tae!

312
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,733
Why, Ms. Bu Se Mi?

313
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,567
Miss.

314
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:16,643
The Commercial Lease Act changed. You
have to guarantee the lease for 10 years.

315
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:20,343
And during those 10 years, you can
only raise the rent by 5% annually.

316
00:21:20,367 --> 00:21:21,743
You didn't know that?

317
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:23,743
Is that true, Miss?

318
00:21:23,767 --> 00:21:26,467
We've only been here for 4 years.

319
00:21:27,533 --> 00:21:30,776
So what?

320
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,743
Don't you think it's too low to threaten

321
00:21:33,767 --> 00:21:36,209
people in business using their sales?

322
00:21:36,233 --> 00:21:37,576
Too low?

323
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,376
When did I threaten anyone?

324
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,743
When did I threaten? I
never threatened anyone.

325
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:43,876
Seems like your memory's failing.

326
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:47,209
You offered me just 3 million won
to leave the kindergarten.

327
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:50,367
- You darn...
- I told you I refused.

328
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,843
What are you looking at?

329
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:55,343
What's with the glare, huh?

330
00:21:55,367 --> 00:21:56,876
What's with the glare?

331
00:21:56,900 --> 00:22:00,843
Did you offer money again to make her quit?

332
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:02,909
No, she didn't take it.

333
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:05,743
So I didn't give it, right?

334
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:07,176
And Miss.

335
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,543
Are you that rich?

336
00:22:08,567 --> 00:22:10,909
I don't know how much money you have.

337
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:14,109
But in Muchang, follow Muchang's rules!

338
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:16,509
- Stop this.
- Hey.

339
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:17,976
Jeon Dong Min grabbed my hand again.

340
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,509
Huh? Saw that? Hey, you saw that!

341
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:21,143
Arrest him. Arrest him.

342
00:22:21,167 --> 00:22:23,400
Hey, the drunk's disturbance comes first.

343
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:28,443
Why are you picking on only me, huh?

344
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:30,976
Why are you singling me out?

345
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,909
Why are you ostracizing just me?

346
00:22:32,933 --> 00:22:36,176
What did I do wrong, huh?

347
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,309
Seong Tae.

348
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:40,376
- Why do you hate and ignore only me?
- Don't get upset.

349
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,076
- Ugh, fine.
- Was I that wrong?

350
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:46,143
If your father saw you like this,
he'd rise from his grave.

351
00:22:46,167 --> 00:22:50,209
Village Chief, why suddenly bring up
my hardworking father?

352
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:52,109
- My father...
- Everyone out! Take him away!

353
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,309
What did my father do that's so terrible?

354
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:57,133
Why are you grabbing my leg?

355
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,443
By the way,

356
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:04,567
why don't you use your
real name at the factory?

357
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:08,467
Only you know it.

358
00:23:09,367 --> 00:23:10,676
[Kim Hye Ja] This is my original name.

359
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:11,976
I legally changed it.

360
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,176
Ah, Kim Hye Ja?

361
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,843
Yeah.

362
00:23:15,867 --> 00:23:17,743
It didn't suit me at all.

363
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:22,109
It's a 'nation's mom'
name, but that's not me.

364
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:24,800
So you do have a conscience, huh.

365
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:31,909
You have a talent for twisting words.

366
00:23:31,933 --> 00:23:33,943
Ah, unnie...

367
00:23:33,967 --> 00:23:36,267
Should I get you some coffee?

368
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:38,976
Yes!

369
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,409
And keep calling me So Yeong unnie.

370
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:43,643
When someone changes their name,
you should call them by it a lot.

371
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:45,409
Okay, I will!

372
00:23:45,433 --> 00:23:48,167
So Yeong unnie!

373
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,276
- Oh my, what's wrong?
- What are you doing?

374
00:23:58,300 --> 00:23:59,967
What?

375
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,800
What is it?

376
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:08,600
I don't recognize who's who here, jeez.

377
00:24:13,667 --> 00:24:15,333
Excuse me.

378
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:19,643
Me?

379
00:24:19,667 --> 00:24:23,300
Don't you know you can't enter
without proper hygiene gear?

380
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,900
I'm the exception.

381
00:24:32,233 --> 00:24:35,733
Are you the company president or something?

382
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:39,067
Not president...

383
00:24:42,633 --> 00:24:44,400
Vice president.

384
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,243
[Kim Hye Ja]

385
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:48,143
Ms. Kim Hye Ja.

386
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:53,333
So Yeong unnie, your coffee.

387
00:24:55,533 --> 00:24:57,209
So Yeong left earlier.

388
00:24:57,233 --> 00:24:59,543
But, you said to use the name often.

389
00:24:59,567 --> 00:25:00,743
My, you're peculiar.

390
00:25:00,767 --> 00:25:01,776
So Yeong unnie.

391
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,200
I said So Yeong left already.

392
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:08,267
Ms. Kim So Yeong?

393
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:14,567
Your face looks unfamiliar.

394
00:25:15,533 --> 00:25:17,167
Have I

395
00:25:18,333 --> 00:25:20,467
ever borrowed money from you?

396
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:26,909
Or bought vinyl flooring?

397
00:25:26,933 --> 00:25:29,100
Flooring...

398
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:33,043
If neither...

399
00:25:33,067 --> 00:25:34,276
Then you're worse.

400
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:35,309
Oh, my.

401
00:25:35,333 --> 00:25:37,376
Unnie.

402
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,776
You got a sharp tongue, huh?

403
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,567
Walk slowly!

404
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:44,467
You'll hurt your joints.

405
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:15,776
- Kids, let's go.
- I made this myself. Share it with Dong Min.

406
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:17,609
Miss, Miss.

407
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,276
We'll head in first now.

408
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,609
- Going home?
- Yes.

409
00:26:20,633 --> 00:26:21,843
Ah, okay.

410
00:26:21,867 --> 00:26:24,267
- Did you have fun?
- Let's go.

411
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:26,543
Miss.

412
00:26:26,567 --> 00:26:30,133
You know how grateful
we are that you came, right?

413
00:26:31,433 --> 00:26:32,609
Miss.

414
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:35,443
Please take good care
of our kids from now on.

415
00:26:35,467 --> 00:26:38,443
Please look after our Jenny
and Seo Hyeon too, Miss.

416
00:26:38,467 --> 00:26:40,309
Thank you for the meal today.

417
00:26:40,333 --> 00:26:41,376
We'll head back now.

418
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,776
Yes, go home quickly.

419
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:43,777
- We'll be going in.
- Okay.

420
00:26:43,801 --> 00:26:45,443
- Thank you.
- Go on inside.

421
00:26:45,467 --> 00:26:46,876
- Goodbye.
- I'll go in now.

422
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:49,600
- Please go in.
- Goodbye.

423
00:26:50,367 --> 00:26:52,376
Jeon Dong Min.

424
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:55,176
Seems like you've got competition now?

425
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,933
What do you mean?

426
00:26:58,067 --> 00:27:02,676
Who in Muchang could stand up
to Seong Tae so confidently?

427
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:06,776
Actually, everyone here is tied to
Seong Tae through interests,

428
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:09,333
so they say 'yes' even when they hate it.

429
00:27:11,133 --> 00:27:14,767
She's truly an unpredictable person.

430
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,267
Look at this.

431
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:21,709
The village chief gave
me this before leaving.

432
00:27:21,733 --> 00:27:22,876
Let's have one more drink.

433
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:25,243
Sis, you should drink with us too.

434
00:27:25,267 --> 00:27:27,076
You guys drink among yourselves.

435
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:29,776
I have to close up the shop.

436
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:30,809
Oh my, Hae Na.

437
00:27:30,833 --> 00:27:33,476
Mom drank too much,
so I can't carry you home.

438
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:36,343
Alright, let's go home and sleep.

439
00:27:36,367 --> 00:27:38,209
My daughter, can you walk?

440
00:27:38,233 --> 00:27:40,709
- Go carefully, sis.
- Yeah, I'm going.

441
00:27:40,733 --> 00:27:41,976
Goodnight, Uncle.

442
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,876
- Goodbye, Hae Na.
- Bye.

443
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:47,509
Oh, Miss, goodbye.

444
00:27:47,533 --> 00:27:49,133
Let's go.

445
00:27:55,733 --> 00:27:57,467
Ms. Hye Ji.

446
00:27:58,333 --> 00:27:59,343
What?

447
00:27:59,367 --> 00:28:03,909
How about we share a glass
of ginseng liquor together?

448
00:28:03,933 --> 00:28:06,109
Speaking of this ginseng liquor,

449
00:28:06,133 --> 00:28:08,509
since it's made with
six-year-old ginseng roots,

450
00:28:08,533 --> 00:28:11,509
just one sip will make
your body temperature...

451
00:28:11,533 --> 00:28:12,976
This, it's really good.

452
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,667
Your temperature spikes?

453
00:28:16,833 --> 00:28:19,043
Can't do that.

454
00:28:19,067 --> 00:28:20,044
Huh?

455
00:28:20,068 --> 00:28:24,176
Because if I get cute,

456
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,876
it'll be a big problem.

457
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:27,043
Can't do that.

458
00:28:27,067 --> 00:28:28,443
No, I can't...

459
00:28:28,467 --> 00:28:29,476
That would be dangerous.

460
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:30,876
- That's really dangerous.
- I'm in danger.

461
00:28:30,900 --> 00:28:32,643
I can't resist cute things.

462
00:28:32,667 --> 00:28:34,643
I can't handle cute stuff at all.

463
00:28:34,667 --> 00:28:37,209
You're already cute enough.
What's with making it worse?

464
00:28:37,233 --> 00:28:40,809
- You're dangerous.
- Dangerous things are bad.

465
00:28:40,833 --> 00:28:41,943
Shall we open it?

466
00:28:41,967 --> 00:28:43,243
- Shall we open it?
- Shall we?

467
00:28:43,267 --> 00:28:44,900
Wait.

468
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,976
- Why? Please.
- Wait a second, friend.

469
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,476
You seem way too drunk right now.

470
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:51,109
- No.
- We'll go in first.

471
00:28:51,133 --> 00:28:52,443
We're too tired.

472
00:28:52,467 --> 00:28:53,776
It seems like she's in good condition.

473
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,867
No, Yeong Ran.

474
00:28:56,567 --> 00:28:58,743
- Feeling sick?
- I'm just...

475
00:28:58,767 --> 00:29:00,967
Today, I'm just going to.

476
00:29:03,033 --> 00:29:05,167
I'll try being cute.

477
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,309
You are gonna get all cute.

478
00:29:09,333 --> 00:29:12,167
You are gonna get all cute.

479
00:29:13,033 --> 00:29:14,776
You are gonna get all cute.

480
00:29:14,800 --> 00:29:16,343
- Like it?
- Like it.

481
00:29:16,367 --> 00:29:17,376
I like it.

482
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:19,709
- You're really...
- Me?

483
00:29:19,733 --> 00:29:22,043
- You're dead.
- I'm dead, really?

484
00:29:22,067 --> 00:29:26,209
Her friend's so cute. She's my ideal type.

485
00:29:26,233 --> 00:29:28,176
She's cute?

486
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,743
Go home and sleep.

487
00:29:29,767 --> 00:29:31,867
I'm going to put Ju Won to sleep.

488
00:29:33,367 --> 00:29:35,876
And take care of her when you come in.

489
00:29:35,900 --> 00:29:36,909
Her mouth's going numb.

490
00:29:36,933 --> 00:29:38,276
Why?

491
00:29:38,300 --> 00:29:41,243
Her mouth is already going numb.

492
00:29:41,267 --> 00:29:43,309
Take off your wig before sleeping.

493
00:29:43,333 --> 00:29:45,433
Not taking it off to sleep?

494
00:29:46,533 --> 00:29:48,509
By the way, my friend!

495
00:29:48,533 --> 00:29:52,809
What's the Muchang strawberry guy like?

496
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:55,976
Back in Seoul I couldn't even speak to him.

497
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,367
He's the most dangerous person in Muchang.

498
00:29:59,933 --> 00:30:02,300
So you should be careful too, Baek Hye Ji.

499
00:30:05,767 --> 00:30:09,867
I knew he was dangerous.

500
00:30:10,900 --> 00:30:14,167
He's super lethal.

501
00:30:19,133 --> 00:30:23,433
Berry, berry, strawberry pie.

502
00:30:48,967 --> 00:30:51,100
I've never used this before.

503
00:30:52,467 --> 00:30:54,067
But this thing

504
00:30:55,667 --> 00:30:59,043
can pierce someone's skull.

505
00:30:59,067 --> 00:31:00,900
Right, Ms. Kim So Yeong?

506
00:31:03,133 --> 00:31:05,009
I don't know about that.

507
00:31:05,033 --> 00:31:08,233
What exactly do you want, Vice President?

508
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:13,643
I keep asking you, right?

509
00:31:13,667 --> 00:31:17,243
Who got you two jobs?

510
00:31:17,267 --> 00:31:18,244
At our factory.

511
00:31:18,268 --> 00:31:20,109
How many times do I have to tell you?

512
00:31:20,133 --> 00:31:23,543
A lawyer came and told me
to do this or go to prison.

513
00:31:23,567 --> 00:31:26,200
Wasn't it Kim Yeong Ran?

514
00:31:28,133 --> 00:31:30,009
Do you like Yeong Ran?

515
00:31:30,033 --> 00:31:34,409
Why keep looking for
Yeong Ran since earlier?

516
00:31:34,433 --> 00:31:37,976
You two aren't involved, are you?

517
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,300
Not me, but with my father.

518
00:31:41,933 --> 00:31:42,943
If it's your father...

519
00:31:42,967 --> 00:31:44,576
Darn it.

520
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,976
Are you genuinely asking
because you don't know?

521
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:48,443
I'm asking because I don't know!

522
00:31:48,467 --> 00:31:52,633
Your darn daughter Kim Yeong Ran
married Chairman Ga Sung Ho.

523
00:31:53,533 --> 00:31:55,909
Haven't you seen the news?

524
00:31:55,933 --> 00:31:57,576
Oh my.

525
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,909
Was this my lottery jackpot?

526
00:31:59,933 --> 00:32:01,676
That's insane!

527
00:32:01,700 --> 00:32:02,909
That gold digger?

528
00:32:02,933 --> 00:32:04,143
Oh goodness.

529
00:32:04,167 --> 00:32:06,043
How can a mother call
her daughter a gold digger?

530
00:32:06,067 --> 00:32:08,043
Ugh, seriously...

531
00:32:08,067 --> 00:32:11,909
Everyone calls her that. Why shouldn't I?

532
00:32:11,933 --> 00:32:15,533
But if my daughter's
Chairman Ga Sung Ho's wife,

533
00:32:16,500 --> 00:32:19,533
then you and I are now...

534
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:21,909
In-laws?

535
00:32:21,933 --> 00:32:24,209
In-laws?

536
00:32:24,233 --> 00:32:27,443
If Yeong Ran's his mother,

537
00:32:27,467 --> 00:32:30,543
you and him aren't in-laws.

538
00:32:30,567 --> 00:32:32,976
It's grandson and grandmother.

539
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,600
Legally speaking.

540
00:32:35,733 --> 00:32:37,076
Oh.

541
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:38,767
Right.

542
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:42,000
In-laws, yep.

543
00:32:42,667 --> 00:32:43,909
In-laws.

544
00:32:43,933 --> 00:32:46,009
You really don't know
where your daughter is?

545
00:32:46,033 --> 00:32:49,043
- Grandmother.
- Darn it.

546
00:32:49,067 --> 00:32:52,176
Didn't you chaebols even investigate that?

547
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:56,100
I cut ties with Yeong Ran long ago.

548
00:32:56,800 --> 00:33:01,643
How is it that these things are the same
for both wealthy and poor families?

549
00:33:01,667 --> 00:33:03,367
Right, in-law?

550
00:33:04,033 --> 00:33:05,667
Exactly.

551
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,409
In-law buddy.

552
00:33:09,433 --> 00:33:13,743
I might find out where Yeong Ran is.

553
00:33:13,767 --> 00:33:15,209
You know how?

554
00:33:15,233 --> 00:33:17,000
If there's a way?

555
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:20,433
Then what will you do for me?

556
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,643
Wait, in-law.

557
00:33:25,667 --> 00:33:27,976
Trying to profit by selling your daughter?

558
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:30,667
Since family's asking to find her,

559
00:33:31,633 --> 00:33:34,609
I might help a little.

560
00:33:34,633 --> 00:33:36,867
Right? Between us?

561
00:33:38,967 --> 00:33:41,143
That's right.

562
00:33:41,167 --> 00:33:43,000
That much is possible between us.

563
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,909
But, in-law.

564
00:33:46,933 --> 00:33:48,209
Huh?

565
00:33:48,233 --> 00:33:50,167
Why are you suddenly

566
00:33:51,633 --> 00:33:55,867
using informal language and causing a fuss?

567
00:33:57,633 --> 00:34:01,000
You really make me want to kill you.

568
00:34:07,033 --> 00:34:10,133
Hey, get someone to follow Lee Don.

569
00:34:11,567 --> 00:34:13,276
Hey.

570
00:34:13,300 --> 00:34:14,967
You watch him.

571
00:34:46,267 --> 00:34:48,200
What are you doing now?

572
00:34:48,867 --> 00:34:51,809
We still haven't
finished our talk yesterday, right?

573
00:34:51,833 --> 00:34:53,533
What about?

574
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,509
We talked about everything yesterday.

575
00:34:56,533 --> 00:34:57,909
What exactly did we talk about?

576
00:34:57,933 --> 00:34:59,943
You know, when I pushed you.

577
00:34:59,967 --> 00:35:02,043
You want to discuss that now?

578
00:35:02,067 --> 00:35:03,409
You're heading to the greenhouse, right?

579
00:35:03,433 --> 00:35:05,143
Let's finish talking there.

580
00:35:05,167 --> 00:35:06,609
What?

581
00:35:06,633 --> 00:35:08,400
Not leaving?

582
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,233
Miss.

583
00:35:30,433 --> 00:35:34,467
Please listen and don't misunderstand.

584
00:35:35,167 --> 00:35:37,676
I genuinely have no interest in you.

585
00:35:37,700 --> 00:35:40,709
That's why I said it meant nothing.

586
00:35:40,733 --> 00:35:43,643
But I'm actually interested in you.

587
00:35:43,667 --> 00:35:45,309
What?

588
00:35:45,333 --> 00:35:48,709
Is that truly the reason?

589
00:35:48,733 --> 00:35:49,876
Yes.

590
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:52,333
Because you doubt me too much.

591
00:35:53,367 --> 00:35:55,509
So you tried to kiss me?

592
00:35:55,533 --> 00:35:58,143
Kiss? When did I?

593
00:35:58,167 --> 00:36:00,043
You were trying to use money
to win people's hearts,

594
00:36:00,067 --> 00:36:01,776
and since money doesn't work on me,

595
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,743
you tried to use your looks

596
00:36:03,767 --> 00:36:06,367
and approached me yesterday.

597
00:36:16,900 --> 00:36:20,076
I see how you might think that way.

598
00:36:20,100 --> 00:36:21,243
Well, Ju Won's father,

599
00:36:21,267 --> 00:36:23,876
you seem deeply mistaken about something.

600
00:36:23,900 --> 00:36:27,076
Since you kept blocking my path,

601
00:36:27,100 --> 00:36:30,643
I instinctively pushed you in panic.

602
00:36:30,667 --> 00:36:32,109
You should've just said that.

603
00:36:32,133 --> 00:36:35,176
I didn't know you would
misunderstand it this much.

604
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:39,509
You have a kid, and yet
you're surprisingly naive.

605
00:36:39,533 --> 00:36:43,200
Not naive, just honest.

606
00:36:47,933 --> 00:36:51,233
So, all misunderstandings are cleared?

607
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,567
We're at the greenhouse.

608
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:06,143
Wow.

609
00:37:06,167 --> 00:37:07,144
[Muchang Residents' Relationship Chart]

610
00:37:07,168 --> 00:37:09,000
What's this?

611
00:37:10,433 --> 00:37:13,233
But why is Berry Boy an 'extra'?

612
00:37:14,667 --> 00:37:16,433
He's the main character.

613
00:37:38,233 --> 00:37:39,833
Huh?

614
00:38:07,333 --> 00:38:10,200
She locked all of this too?

615
00:38:11,733 --> 00:38:13,400
000.

616
00:38:14,100 --> 00:38:15,833
No.

617
00:38:27,100 --> 00:38:30,467
Oh, come on.

618
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,600
Wow!

619
00:38:50,467 --> 00:38:52,167
What is it?

620
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,267
Jeez.

621
00:39:28,367 --> 00:39:31,009
Ah, be careful when picking them.

622
00:39:31,033 --> 00:39:32,709
They wilt fast if the stems fall off.

623
00:39:32,733 --> 00:39:34,533
And it lowers their market value.

624
00:39:36,867 --> 00:39:38,633
Oh, this.

625
00:39:39,467 --> 00:39:41,700
You owe me 10,000 won.

626
00:39:43,733 --> 00:39:44,843
Then I'll pay you back now.

627
00:39:44,867 --> 00:39:46,943
I hate owing people more than
anything in this world.

628
00:39:46,967 --> 00:39:50,433
Oh, you're not letting me speak.

629
00:39:58,833 --> 00:40:01,976
Isn't it hard for you to
raise Ju Won alone?

630
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,633
Me?

631
00:40:04,933 --> 00:40:06,843
Well, I

632
00:40:06,867 --> 00:40:10,167
I want to be like a greenhouse for Ju Won.

633
00:40:11,133 --> 00:40:13,043
What do you mean by that?

634
00:40:13,067 --> 00:40:17,943
Strawberries are sensitive
to temperature and humidity.

635
00:40:17,967 --> 00:40:20,843
But this greenhouse stands firm,

636
00:40:20,867 --> 00:40:23,043
blocking rain, wind, and cold.

637
00:40:23,067 --> 00:40:24,976
It protects them from all that.

638
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,833
Feels secure, doesn't it?

639
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:32,333
Ju Won's lucky

640
00:40:33,033 --> 00:40:34,967
to have a father like you.

641
00:40:41,300 --> 00:40:42,900
Miss.

642
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:47,567
I'm sorry for misunderstanding you earlier.

643
00:40:48,433 --> 00:40:51,009
You didn't even take the
money Seong Tae offered.

644
00:40:51,033 --> 00:40:53,067
Never seen anyone refuse that.

645
00:40:53,733 --> 00:40:56,043
It's only 3 million won, after all.

646
00:40:56,067 --> 00:40:58,967
3 million won isn't
going to change my life.

647
00:41:01,700 --> 00:41:02,809
Wow.

648
00:41:02,833 --> 00:41:06,276
Even though you speak so annoyingly,

649
00:41:06,300 --> 00:41:08,433
you seem to have a good heart.

650
00:41:20,267 --> 00:41:21,509
Alright.

651
00:41:21,533 --> 00:41:23,709
I think we've had enough.

652
00:41:23,733 --> 00:41:25,600
Let's go have breakfast.

653
00:41:30,167 --> 00:41:32,309
Is 50,000 won enough for this?

654
00:41:32,333 --> 00:41:33,967
Come on.

655
00:41:34,667 --> 00:41:36,609
Solving everything with money

656
00:41:36,633 --> 00:41:38,509
doesn't work on me.

657
00:41:38,533 --> 00:41:39,809
Eat that as dessert.

658
00:41:39,833 --> 00:41:41,467
Here.

659
00:41:55,767 --> 00:41:57,543
Why?

660
00:41:57,567 --> 00:41:59,709
Changed your mind?

661
00:41:59,733 --> 00:42:01,533
Should I give you money?

662
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,533
No.

663
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:10,133
Let's go.

664
00:42:19,067 --> 00:42:23,809
When did you get that scar?

665
00:42:23,833 --> 00:42:25,609
Scar?

666
00:42:25,633 --> 00:42:27,667
There's a scar on your wrist.

667
00:42:29,733 --> 00:42:31,833
This isn't a scar.

668
00:42:33,700 --> 00:42:37,933
Oh, everyone has a scar or two, right?

669
00:42:40,267 --> 00:42:42,176
Lower your shirt now.

670
00:42:42,200 --> 00:42:44,300
Nice abs, by the way.

671
00:42:45,367 --> 00:42:47,767
I wasn't showing them off.

672
00:42:56,500 --> 00:42:58,900
Sis, what's going on this morning?

673
00:42:59,867 --> 00:43:01,633
Is something good happening?

674
00:43:06,100 --> 00:43:07,709
Seon Woo.

675
00:43:07,733 --> 00:43:09,700
Did you find Kim So Yeong?

676
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:15,800
How did you know?

677
00:43:18,100 --> 00:43:19,609
Sis.

678
00:43:19,633 --> 00:43:22,309
I'm working hard to catch Kim Yeong Ran.

679
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:25,133
I'll bring her to you. Don't worry.

680
00:43:28,133 --> 00:43:30,043
Is having a child just for show?

681
00:43:30,067 --> 00:43:32,209
You'll quit after having a kid.
Why take parental leave?

682
00:43:32,233 --> 00:43:33,443
Quit now!

683
00:43:33,467 --> 00:43:36,076
I said quit!

684
00:43:36,100 --> 00:43:37,833
Ga Seon Woo.

685
00:43:37,942 --> 00:43:47,930
Officail Website : kissasia.id

686
00:43:47,954 --> 00:43:57,942
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

687
00:43:39,967 --> 00:43:41,600
Sis.

688
00:43:44,033 --> 00:43:45,843
This is...

689
00:43:45,867 --> 00:43:48,109
Not a single word you said was wrong.

690
00:43:48,133 --> 00:43:49,876
Is having a baby just a show?

691
00:43:49,900 --> 00:43:52,876
I also don't like how anyone
and everyone takes maternity leave,

692
00:43:52,900 --> 00:43:56,009
gives birth, and quits,
causing harm to the company.

693
00:43:56,033 --> 00:43:58,109
I hate it too.

694
00:43:58,133 --> 00:43:59,576
Right?

695
00:43:59,600 --> 00:44:02,676
I did good, didn't I?

696
00:44:02,700 --> 00:44:04,833
- Seon Woo.
- Yeah.

697
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:12,409
I always say,

698
00:44:12,433 --> 00:44:15,367
'Don't show your true self

699
00:44:16,167 --> 00:44:18,900
to those idiots.'

700
00:44:26,567 --> 00:44:27,809
Sis.

701
00:44:27,833 --> 00:44:29,243
Sis, I get it.

702
00:44:29,267 --> 00:44:31,309
I'll take care of this right away, okay?

703
00:44:31,333 --> 00:44:34,376
Hey, get this done through
the secretary's office.

704
00:44:34,400 --> 00:44:36,033
It's done, right?

705
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:42,567
If you let pigs disrespect you,
you become one. Understood?

706
00:44:43,467 --> 00:44:45,243
Answer.

707
00:44:45,267 --> 00:44:46,676
Okay.

708
00:44:46,700 --> 00:44:49,333
I'll really follow your advice now.

709
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:52,943
Seon Woo.

710
00:44:52,967 --> 00:44:55,376
Cancel the party and starve for three days.

711
00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:59,209
Don't shave. Apologize
publicly looking haggard.

712
00:44:59,233 --> 00:45:00,709
Understand?

713
00:45:00,733 --> 00:45:01,976
Okay.

714
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:04,376
I always listen to everything you say, sis.

715
00:45:04,400 --> 00:45:06,433
- Follow me.
- Huh?

716
00:45:20,133 --> 00:45:22,143
- Yes?
- Attorney Lee Don?

717
00:45:22,167 --> 00:45:23,144
Yeah, that's me.

718
00:45:23,168 --> 00:45:24,800
We are the police.

719
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:28,976
I don't need an introduction, I know.

720
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:32,743
You're under urgent arrest
for embezzlement charges.

721
00:45:32,767 --> 00:45:36,800
Embezzlement. How cliché.

722
00:45:38,900 --> 00:45:41,333
Huh? Vice Chairman!

723
00:45:43,133 --> 00:45:44,143
I saw that your video is popular online.

724
00:45:44,167 --> 00:45:45,609
Congratulations.

725
00:45:45,633 --> 00:45:46,876
Congratulations?

726
00:45:46,900 --> 00:45:48,500
Ga Seon Woo!

727
00:45:49,333 --> 00:45:52,409
What brings you here this early?

728
00:45:52,433 --> 00:45:55,543
You didn't come out of
concern for me, did you?

729
00:45:55,567 --> 00:45:57,443
Are you here to watch me get arrested?

730
00:45:57,467 --> 00:45:59,300
To warn you.

731
00:46:00,067 --> 00:46:02,076
Taking down that video is no big deal.

732
00:46:02,100 --> 00:46:05,576
People easily forgive the privileged
who abuse power.

733
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:09,609
But they just can't forgive the ones
who have nothing but lack integrity.

734
00:46:09,633 --> 00:46:14,400
The lawyer of Chairman Ga Sung Ho, who wanted to
become a tycoon through coins and embezzlement.

735
00:46:15,200 --> 00:46:17,267
How's that for a news
headline, Attorney Lee?

736
00:46:18,800 --> 00:46:20,843
I may not have money,

737
00:46:20,867 --> 00:46:23,667
but I still have my conscience, Professor.

738
00:46:25,233 --> 00:46:27,600
Everyone's yapping about
conscience these days.

739
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,167
Attorney Lee.

740
00:46:32,900 --> 00:46:35,400
Where did you hide Kim Yeong Ran?

741
00:46:38,833 --> 00:46:42,109
The right to remain silent is used
in situations like this, right?

742
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:44,376
Give me a moment.

743
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:46,676
Shouldn't you at least
let me put on clothes?

744
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:48,909
Right?

745
00:46:48,933 --> 00:46:51,033
Darn it, that punk...

746
00:47:12,800 --> 00:47:14,176
Good day.

747
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:15,576
Hey, Butler Choi.

748
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:17,976
Contact me immediately
once you find the will. Understood?

749
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:20,400
Understood, Vice President.

750
00:47:21,367 --> 00:47:22,509
Professor.

751
00:47:22,533 --> 00:47:25,300
Can we work together again?

752
00:47:26,767 --> 00:47:30,309
The owner never fired you,
so this isn't reemployment.

753
00:47:30,333 --> 00:47:32,609
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

754
00:47:32,633 --> 00:47:33,643
Let's go, Cheol Su.

755
00:47:33,667 --> 00:47:35,176
Yes, Butler.

756
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:37,509
Thank you.

757
00:47:37,533 --> 00:47:39,167
Thank you.

758
00:47:44,367 --> 00:47:46,109
This familiar feel.

759
00:47:46,133 --> 00:47:48,476
I can't tell you how much I missed this.

760
00:47:48,500 --> 00:47:50,309
Butler.

761
00:47:50,333 --> 00:47:53,200
We should find the will first.

762
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:57,676
You check the second floor.

763
00:47:57,700 --> 00:48:00,076
I'll start searching the first floor.

764
00:48:00,100 --> 00:48:01,967
Understood.

765
00:48:05,667 --> 00:48:07,243
Jeez.

766
00:48:07,267 --> 00:48:10,600
Look at this mess since
I've been gone. Huh?

767
00:48:11,800 --> 00:48:13,400
Huh?

768
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:17,233
What?

769
00:48:21,067 --> 00:48:24,367
Who put soju in here?

770
00:48:37,967 --> 00:48:39,767
[Teacher Bu Se Mi] PLAN B.

771
00:48:44,700 --> 00:48:48,733
[Muchang Strawberries]

772
00:48:50,767 --> 00:48:53,409
[Attorney Lee: PLAN B]

773
00:48:53,433 --> 00:48:55,867
Mr. Dong Min, here are the strawberries.

774
00:49:05,500 --> 00:49:06,943
My friend.

775
00:49:06,967 --> 00:49:09,400
I borrowed your clothes because I had none.

776
00:49:14,567 --> 00:49:15,843
Dong Min!

777
00:49:15,867 --> 00:49:16,909
Yes?

778
00:49:16,933 --> 00:49:19,776
Would you mind going to town with me?

779
00:49:19,800 --> 00:49:22,243
I need someone familiar
with the area to escort me.

780
00:49:22,267 --> 00:49:24,100
I need to cook.

781
00:49:24,967 --> 00:49:26,509
Okay.

782
00:49:26,533 --> 00:49:29,333
I'm free.

783
00:49:32,267 --> 00:49:33,776
Do you have a car?

784
00:49:33,800 --> 00:49:35,709
A car?

785
00:49:35,733 --> 00:49:37,933
Wait, hold on.

786
00:50:06,833 --> 00:50:09,200
Only picked misfits like herself.

787
00:50:13,800 --> 00:50:14,843
Dong Min!

788
00:50:14,867 --> 00:50:16,876
Dong Min, I'm borrowing your car.

789
00:50:16,900 --> 00:50:18,900
Dong Min, how do I look?

790
00:50:20,567 --> 00:50:22,476
Oh, nice socks.

791
00:50:22,500 --> 00:50:23,477
Huh? Really?

792
00:50:23,501 --> 00:50:26,509
I should show these to Hye Ji.
How should I show it?

793
00:50:26,533 --> 00:50:29,109
The accelerator's on
the right, yeah? I'm off!

794
00:50:29,133 --> 00:50:30,143
Hey, drive safe!

795
00:50:30,167 --> 00:50:31,343
Yeah.

796
00:50:31,367 --> 00:50:34,300
[Village Bus Schedule]

797
00:50:37,500 --> 00:50:39,743
[Dongwaru]

798
00:50:39,767 --> 00:50:40,744
Dongwaru.

799
00:50:40,768 --> 00:50:44,276
[Dongwaru]

800
00:50:44,300 --> 00:50:45,277
Jeez.

801
00:50:45,301 --> 00:50:47,243
What's wrong?

802
00:50:47,267 --> 00:50:49,676
What if there's a fly in the restaurant?

803
00:50:49,700 --> 00:50:51,143
Ma'am.

804
00:50:51,167 --> 00:50:52,509
Miss.

805
00:50:52,533 --> 00:50:56,200
Can I borrow your motorcycle?

806
00:51:00,667 --> 00:51:01,976
- Tae Min.
- Yes?

807
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:06,243
We've shopped enough. Let's eat.

808
00:51:06,267 --> 00:51:07,976
Any famous restaurants around here?

809
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:11,400
There's a great place.
Just trust me, Hye Ji.

810
00:51:13,433 --> 00:51:14,776
[Dongwaru] Hye Ji.

811
00:51:14,800 --> 00:51:19,443
Here's a 30-year-old traditional hand-made
noodle shop. It's made only by Grandma's hands...

812
00:51:19,467 --> 00:51:22,209
No, no, Grandma makes it by hand.

813
00:51:22,233 --> 00:51:24,176
You should come this way.

814
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:25,876
